# ─── profile: cosmos-nvidia ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ⚠ UNVERIFIED TEMPLATE — NOT REAL COSMOS CONFIG (as of 2026-06-27).
#   Every value below is an EXPECTED default, not a measured one. cosmos has not
#   yet been inspected. Do NOT trust these for benchmarking or as a record of how
#   cosmos actually runs. Capture the real values first:
#       scripts/cosmos/capture-cosmos.sh   (run on cosmos; see scripts/cosmos/README.md)
#   then replace the placeholders here and fill docs/reference/development-machine-cosmos.md.
#
# Home workstation. NVIDIA GPU, native Linux. A local Linux Ollama is EXPECTED to
# serve the GPU directly (no host-offload hop), matching the committed script
# defaults — confirm at home.
#
# ACTIVATE:  cp profiles/cosmos-nvidia.env .env   (then append ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=...)
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Local Linux Ollama serves the NVIDIA GPU directly.
OLLAMA_HOSTS="http://localhost:11434"

# Both vision models are installed on cosmos (qwen primary + minicpm comparison).
LAWNLORD_MODELS="qwen2.5vl:7b minicpm-v:latest"

# Workers. Server runs NUM_PARALLEL=1 by default, so 1; raise only if Ollama is
# launched with a matching NUM_PARALLEL.
LAWNLORD_WORKERS=1

# llamacpp_server.sh (Linux/CUDA vision server) paths — confirm at home:
# OLLAMA_LIB=/usr/local/lib/ollama   # Ollama's bundled llama-server + CUDA libs
# MODEL=qwen2.5vl:7b
# PORT=18082
# CTX=8192
